@startuml
title Widget Basics - Beginner View

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Widget {
	+ setGeometry(rect)
	+ activate()
	+ deactivate()
	+ update(tick)
	+ appendRenderUnits(builder)
	# _onUpdate(tick)
	# _onMouse*Event(event)
	# _onKey*Event(event)
	# _buildRenderUnit() : RenderUnit
}

class "Parent widget" as Parent
class "Child widget" as Child
class Rect2D
class UpdateTick
class EventView
class RenderUnit

Widget <|-- Parent
Widget <|-- Child
Parent o-- Child : owns child relationship
Widget --> Rect2D : geometry
Widget --> UpdateTick : receives
Widget --> EventView : receives
Widget --> RenderUnit : builds

note right of Widget
A widget is the main extension point.
Override update, event, and render methods
to create application-specific behavior.
end note

note bottom of Parent
Widgets form a tree. Geometry and activation
affect every child below a widget.
end note

@enduml
